-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">The subscriber chooses a password/password for his account, and it is the responsibility of protecting this password and not sharing or disseminating it to the subscriber. In the event that any transactions occur using this password, the subscriber will bear all the resulting responsibilities, without any responsibility on the Mulzoom website.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; background: white;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">The subscriber bears full responsibility for all of his own content, which he uploads and publishes through the site.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"RTL\" style=\"text-align: right; background: white; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed; margin: 0in 2.4pt 0in 0in;\"><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h4 style=\"margin: 0in; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Register on the site</span></u></span></h4>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Some parts of the site are only open to registered members after providing some personal information about them. When registering, the subscriber agrees </span><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-EG\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">that </span><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">the information provided is complete and accurate, and commits that he will not register on the site and will not attempt to enter it impersonating another subscriber&rsquo;s name and will not use a name that the administration may deem inappropriate or inappropriate, such as phone numbers and impersonated names of famous personalities. Website links, incomprehensible names, and the like.</span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"RTL\" style=\"text-align: right; background: white; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed; margin: 0in 2.4pt 0in 0in;\"><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h4 style=\"margin: 0in; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Use and sharing of information</span></u></span></h4>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; background: white;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">All information provided by users is treated strictly confidential and is not sold or shared with any third party who is not authorized to access it.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; background: white;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Information use cases:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; background: white;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Developing the services provided by the website and our company&rsquo;s various services.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; background: white;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">In the event of contracting with a third party to develop the services we provide after committing not to share any information that conflicts with this privacy statement.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; background: white;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">If we are legally bound by a court order to disclose any information.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"RTL\" style=\"text-align: right; background: white; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed; margin: 0in 2.4pt 0in 0in;\"><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h4 style=\"margin: 0in; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Content censorship</span></u></span></h4>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; background: white;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Malzoom management reserves the right to monitor any content entered by the subscriber, without being obligated to do so. Therefore, it reserves the right (without obligation) to delete, remove or edit any entered materials that would violate the terms and conditions of the site without consulting the user.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"RTL\" style=\"text-align: right; background: white; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed; margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt 0in;\"><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 176, 80);\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; tab-stops: list 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"line-height: 107%; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">*** These terms are constantly updated</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" dir=\"RTL\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: right; tab-stops: list 0in; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"line-height: 107%; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" dir=\"RTL\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: right; tab-stops: list 0in; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"line-height: 107%; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center; line-height: 27.0pt; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\" align=\"center\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">common questions</span></h2>\r\n<p dir=\"RTL\" style=\"text-align: right; background: white; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed; margin: 0in .25in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Client</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"RTL\" style=\"text-align: right; background: white; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed; margin: 0in .25in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">What are the fees charged by the customer?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">The customer does not bear any fees </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">. <br></span><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">As for the obligatory commission, it is deducted from the service provider and not from the customer </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">I registered in Mulzoom and I can\'t log in yet?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">All data must be completely completed in order for your account to be activated. The account can be reviewed first before activation by our workers </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">I registered in Mulzoom and added a job, but it has not appeared yet?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">After adding your request, the support team will review the requested work to ensure that it meets Mazloum&rsquo;s conditions. After that, you will receive a notification once it is approved and it will appear on the main page of all service providers </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">How do I choose from advanced providers?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You can browse the personal accounts of each service provider to read an overview of him and see examples of his work, and through the offer he presents, you can choose what suits you </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Is there a minimum and maximum budget for the work I want to request?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Yes, the minimum is 100 pounds, and there is no maximum budget </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">What are the payment methods in Mazloum?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">We work to provide all payment methods, including credit cards, smart wallets, or cash payment </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Can I modify the work request after adding it?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You can modify the work as long as no service provider applies for it. However, after offers arrive, you cannot modify it, but you can cancel it </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">I saw the provider\'s accounts and was impressed by someone\'s experience. Can I choose them to work on my application?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Yes, through the service provider&rsquo;s account page, you can click on the &ldquo;Ready to work with you&rdquo; button, after which you can add the work that you want him to work on, and you can also make the work generally available to others if the person you have chosen does not agree to work for any reason </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Can I cancel an order I have created?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Currently, if you do not employ anyone, you can only close the business and not cancel it, knowing that you can reopen it again if you wish, knowing that there is a limit to the number of closed projects, which is 3 projects every 30 days </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">After hiring the service provider, the possibility of canceling the work is by agreement with him or by referring to technical support in the event of a disagreement between you. This may lead to not returning the full amount depending on the problem and the technical support&rsquo;s estimate of it </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Why was my job rejected?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">When any work is rejected, an alert is sent to your account containing a request to modify the work in order for it to be accepted. You can directly modify the work and send it again for review instead of adding a new work </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">How many jobs can I add at the same time?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You can add an unlimited number of open jobs</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">But you cannot exceed 3 closed projects within 30 days, which are work that was closed manually by you, or automatically because the service provider was not chosen to work on it </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">I chose to view a service provider but was unable to hire him. Why?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You will not be able to hire any service provider or choose one of the offers for your business unless you charge your account with the value of this offer </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">How can I contact the service provider?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">By hiring the service provider through a button and ready to work with you in his personal account, or by placing the service provider to offer your work, where you can then communicate with him via messages before hiring him </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Can I employ more than one service provider for the same work?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Yes, you can do that, and communication with each of them is completely separate within the service provider </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">When does the business close automatically?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">After 30 days of approval, your business will be automatically closed. You can also reopen the business at any time to receive more offers </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Can I contact the service provider after I receive the job?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You can continue to communicate with the service provider within a period of 60 days from receiving the work from him, noting that receiving the work means that you have obtained everything you wanted and the service provider can receive the amount for the work </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Can I edit a work-in-progress budget?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Yes, you can do that after agreeing with the service provider on the new value and then asking the service provider to request an amendment to the deal value directly from his account. You will then receive a notification of the value and duration of the new deal and you can approve or reject it </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"line-height: 27pt; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in 0.25in; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;Service provider</span></u></strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">From whom is the service provider&rsquo;s platform commission deducted, from the employer or from the service provider?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">The service provider\'s commission is deducted from the service provider and not from the employer. The offer added by the service provider is a final offer from which the service provider\'s commission is deducted </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">How and when can I withdraw my profits from the service provider?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You can request to withdraw profits from the balance page. The currently available methods of withdrawing profits are </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">:</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Electronic wallet</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Direct transfer to your bank account in 7 days, except for the first transfer after 7 working days</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You will be able to withdraw profits after the end of the balance suspension period, which is 7 days. Note that the suspension period begins from the day following the end of work and continues until the end of the seventh day, Cairo time </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You will be able to withdraw the balance directly within a period of 5 working days after the customer evaluates that the work is excellent </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Can I apply for any job offered by the service provider?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You can apply for a job that you have experience working in, noting that you can only submit 10 active offers at the same time, and you will get two additional offers if you verify your identity </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Why can\'t I add new offers to the business?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">At the present time, the service provider can add 12 active offers at the same time, and in order to be able to add a new offer, one of the old offers must be closed, either by closing the work or implementing it by you or by any other service provider </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">. <br></span><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Also, you cannot add a new offer if you have 3 projects under implementation, regardless of the number of current offers you have </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">. <br></span><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Note that you can submit your own job offers that you receive, regardless of the previous numbers </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Why can\'t I add any offers to existing work?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You must add 3 works that you have implemented within your work gallery, while completing the steps to complete the account, such as adding a personal bio and choosing the appropriate specialization </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Can I contact the employer I made an offer to?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Only the employer can communicate with you and then you can respond to him. You will not be able to start communicating with him via messages </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Can I communicate with my employer after I hand over my job?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You can continue to communicate with the employer within a period of 30 days from submitting your work to him </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Can I modify the offer I added to a business?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You can modify the offer within 10 minutes of adding it, and also if the employer contacts you via messages before hiring you for that job </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">. <br></span><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You can also request an amendment to the deal if you agree with the employer during implementation to change the value of the deal, its duration, or the method of payment. After you request the amendment, a notification will arrive to the employer through which he can approve or reject the amendment. Note that you are only allowed to submit 6 amendment requests per transaction </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Why can\'t I add links to my offers?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Unfortunately, this is not allowed. Instead, you can use the portfolio to add your works to your personal profile </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Why was the view I added hidden?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Offers that violate the site policy or are not related to the work to which the offer was added will be hidden </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">I submitted a series of offers on several projects, how can I follow them up?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You can follow it from my show list </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Why do I have a balance that I cannot withdraw?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">The balance on the service provider is of four types </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Total balance </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">: </span><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">It is the entire balance in your withdrawable and non-withdrawal account </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Suspended balance </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">: </span><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">It is the balance that you obtained and has not exceeded 7 days, which is the suspension period before it becomes withdrawable </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Available balance </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">: </span><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">This is the balance with which you have charged your account to create currencies and employ the service provider, and so that you can withdraw it as profits </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Withdrawable balance </span></strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">: </span><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">It is the balance coming from the profits of your business after 7 days have passed after receiving the amount in your account and you can withdraw it </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">What are the reasons for suspending the balance?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">The profits achieved by the service provider are suspended for a period of 7 days, and during this period he cannot use the suspended balance or request a withdrawal until the end of the period for the following reasons </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">:</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">The amounts that employers pay when hiring the service provider take several business days to reach our bank account and become available for sending again. In most cases, it is not possible to send profits before the end of the hold period even if we wanted to because the amount is not yet available for sending</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">The duration of the balance hold is necessary and helps us ensure customer rights and combat fraud attempts. Providing a safe work environment that allows all users to work safely is a top priority for us</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">You will be able to withdraw profits after the end of the balance suspension period, noting that the suspension period begins from the day following the receipt of the work and continues until the end of the fourteenth day GMT </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Why don\'t I see the withdraw balance button?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">The Withdraw Balance button appears when the balance suspension period has expired and the minimum withdrawable balance is available in your account </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<h2 style=\"line-height: 27.0pt; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 15.0pt .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">General</span></u></strong></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Can I delete my account or change my service provider username?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Yes, this is possible in specific cases. Contact us via</span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\"><a href=\"https://support.mostaql.com/conversations\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">m </span></a></span><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">help center </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Who owns the intellectual property rights to projects?</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .25in;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">By default, and unless agreed by the initiator to the contrary, the employer owns all intellectual property rights and copyrights to the projects received through the service provider. The service provider does not have the right to impose additional rights on the work after its implementation or delivery has begun</span></p>'),
(42,'Modules\\BusinessSettingsModule\\Entities\\DataSetting','11c9071f-70e2-412b-ba73-73da0ae9f7cb','en','refund_policy','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background: white; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">. The return process is subject to several conditions, including </span></u></strong><strong><u><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">:</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Symbol;\">&middot;</span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"> </span></strong><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Credits are available for return within a maximum of 14 days from the date of payment if the payment method provides a return option.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The amount will be returned after deducting the electronic payment fees from the amount, in addition to 14% of the fees for each return request.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\"> </span></strong><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The return will be made exclusively to the payment method that was used, as we carry out the </span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Refund process </span></strong><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">for the amounts to be recovered Therefore, we ask you to confirm the method you intend to use before making the payment process, and then contact us through the help center if you wish to restore the balance </span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">.</span></strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!-- [if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br style=\"mso-special-character: line-break;\"><!--[endif]--></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Issuing refunds</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica\',sans-serif;\">1 </span><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">. The processing time for your refund depends on the type of refund and the payment method you used.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">2. The refund period/process begins when Malzoom processes your refund according to your refund type.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">3. The refund amount covers the price of the canceled service or returned product.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Types of refunds</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Malzoom will process your refund according to the following refund types .</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"RTL\" style=\"text-align: right; background: white; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">&nbsp;</span></span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Cancellation Refunds - Refunds are processed once you cancel the service and request a refund. To learn how to return an item, read our returns policy.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">2. Refunds of Canceled Orders - Your refund is automatically activated once your cancellation has been successfully processed.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">3. Refunds for Non-Performance - Refunds are processed once the service is not performed by the Service Provider after agreeing and requesting a refund. To learn how to return an item, read our returns policy.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background: white; margin: 12.0pt 0in 12.0pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif; color: black;\">Payment method for the refund option at the time of refund .</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"line-height: 107%; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">1-Refund debit or credit card transfer On the same debit or credit card 10 working days</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">2-Refund the mobile phone wallet 5 business days from payment</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">3- Refund payment upon receipt within 5 working days , or with a refund voucher, bank transfer, electronic wallet, or purchasing a new service.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Note: The maximum refund timeline does not include weekends and public holidays.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" dir=\"RTL\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: right; line-height: normal; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Methods of describing recovery</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" dir=\"RTL\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: right; line-height: normal; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">&nbsp;</span></span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Bank deposit</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The bank account details provided must be correct. The account must be active and must have some balance.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Debit card or credit card</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">If the refund does not appear on your card statement after the refund is complete and you receive a notification from Mulzoom , please contact your personal bank.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Mobile </span></u></strong><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">wallet</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">As with a bank deposit, the amount will be refunded to the same mobile account details you entered at the time of payment.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Redemption voucher</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Vouchers will be sent to the customer\'s registered email ID on Mulzoom and can be redeemed with the same email ID.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" dir=\"RTL\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: right; line-height: normal; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Important Note: A coupon discount code can only be applied once. The remaining amount will not be refunded or used towards your next purchase even if the order value is less than the value of the voucher.</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" dir=\"RTL\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: right; line-height: normal; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">&nbsp;</span></span></u></strong></span></p>'),
(43,'Modules\\BusinessSettingsModule\\Entities\\DataSetting','514e21aa-ae56-447e-9f9d-a34d4995bb9e','en','cancellation_policy','<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Can I cancel </span></u></strong><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">an order <u>I have created?</u></span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" dir=\"RTL\" style=\"text-align: right; line-height: normal; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"LTR\" lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">&nbsp;</span></span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 15.0pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Currently, if you do not employ anyone, you can only close the work and not cancel it, knowing that you can reopen it again if you wish, knowing that there is a limit to the number of closed applications , which is 3 projects every 30 days </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 15.0pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">After hiring the service provider, the possibility of canceling the work is by agreement with him or by referring to technical support in the event of a disagreement between you. This may lead to not returning the full amount depending on the problem and the technical support&rsquo;s estimate of it </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"RTL\" style=\"text-align: right; background: white; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed; margin: 0in .25in 0in 0in;\"><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"RTL\" style=\"text-align: right; background: white; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed; margin: 0in .25in 0in 0in;\"><span lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The status of requests is in mandatory</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" dir=\"RTL\" style=\"text-align: right; line-height: normal; direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: embed; margin: 12.0pt 0in 0in 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"LTR\" lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">&nbsp;</span></span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 15.0pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">goes through several stages, starting with adding and then receiving offers, and ending with the request being completed and evaluated by the customer or cancellation by the customer or service provider with reasons. We will provide below an explanation of all these stages </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">:</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top: 12.0pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Open order</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 15.0pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The application is in the stage of receiving offers. You will remain able to submit this request and add your offer to it for a period of 21 days from the date of adding the request </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top: 12.0pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Request in progress</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 15.0pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The application enters this stage after your offer is accepted by the applicant and its implementation begins. You will then be able to follow up on all the details related to it </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top: 12.0pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Completed order</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 15.0pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">After completing work on the order according to agreement with the customer, you can send the delivery request for the requester to approve it and the order becomes complete. At this stage, the profits are added to the service provider&rsquo;s balance, and the customer has the right to evaluate the work. After depositing the profits in your balance, they remain suspended for 7 days before you can withdraw them </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top: 12.0pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Closed order</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The request will be closed by its owner only, or automatically after 30 days from the date of publication </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">You will not be able to add your offer to a closed project, but the client will only be able to communicate with the interested parties via messages and accept their previously submitted offers </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 15.0pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\">note </span></strong><strong><span lang=\"EN\">:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">It is possible to reopen the closed order by its owner to continue receiving more offers, and then your offer will return to being active and will be deducted from the total number of offers available in your account </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top: 12.0pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Canceled order</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 15.0pt 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The order can be canceled if it is under implementation by the service provider only, as he can withdraw from the order after explaining his reasons to the customer by submitting a cancellation request for the project. If the customer wants to cancel, he must agree with the person responsible for this or contact the support team. It should be noted that the service provider will not receive any profits from canceled requests, and his request completion rate will decrease after cancellation, and the requester will also have the right to evaluate his performance on this request </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top: 12.0pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><u><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Special request</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Some clients may want to hire specific contractors to carry out their projects, so they create a special project for them. The details of this type of request are visible to the customer and the executing service provider only, and other service providers will not be able to submit their offers on it </span><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in;\"><span dir=\"RTL\" lang=\"AR-SA\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Although they are private projects, their evaluation appears on the service provider&rsquo;s profile and is added to his overall evaluation</span></p>'),
